Mac-n-Cheese Sauce

1 c cashews
3/4 c nutritional yeast
1/4 c oat flour
1/4 c tapioca flour
1 tbsp paprika
1 tbsp sugar
2 tsp powdered mustard
2 tsp sea salt
2 tsp onion powder

Add all ingredients to a food processor and process until a fine powder is formed. There should not be any discernable chunks or large granules of cashews, may take 3-4 min. Store this in a jar or portion out to 1/3 c increments and store in ziplock bags for up to 2 months or refrigerate for up to 6 months. 

To use: Cook 1 c of dry macaroni per package instructions and drain. Combine 1/3 c mix with 1 c water or unsweetened nondairy milk in a saucepan over medium low heat. Bring to a boil while whisking. Simmer for 1 min, then toss with hot cooked pasta.
